# position: sticky; An element with position: sticky; toggles between a relative and fixed position, depending on the scroll position.
 A sticky element is positioned relative until a certain scroll position is reached - then it "sticks" in that place (like position:fixed).
 You must specify at least one of the top, right, bottom or left properties, for sticky positioning to work as 0.



OVERFLOW PROPERTY:-
Whenever we'll have to give the content and it exceeds the size of the box, then we'll be able to correct this by using this property.
overflow: hidden;
This can have the following values:- {visible, hidden, scroll, auto}
# visible - Default. The overflow is not clipped. The content renders outside the element's box
# hidden - The overflow is clipped, and the rest of the content is hidden
# scroll - Scrollbars are added. User must scroll to see all content
# auto - Similar to scroll, but adds scrollbars only when necessary

STYLING LISTS:-
# If we don't need any styling for the list values then we can give the following value: 
 lsit-style: none;
# CSS has the following properties for styling HTML lists:
# list-style-type - Specifies the type of list-item marker.
 It has the following values: {circle, square, disc, upper-roman, lower-roman, lower-alpha, decimal}
# list-style-image - Specifies an image as the list-item marker.
   list-style-image: url('sqpurple.gif');
   list-style-type: square;
# list-style-position - Specifies the position of the list-item markers. It has two values: inside and outside.
 list-style-position: outside; means that the bullet points will be outside the list item. The start of each line of a list item will be aligned vertically. This is default one.
 list-style-position: inside; means that the bullet points will be inside the list item. As it is part of the list item, it will be part of the text and push the text at the start.
# list-style - A shorthand property for the properties above, where all the properties can be used together in one line.
 list-style: square inside url("sqpurple.gif");
This will display the list with image inside the square button.
